low---------------------------------
	text (code) segment
------------------------------------
	data segment (initialized global/static data)
------------------------------------
	bss segment (uninitialized global/static data)
------------------------------------
	heap segment


	stack segment
high--------------------------------


readelf -l XXX.out    /* show ELF program header */
Headers of type LOAD are copied into virtual memory when the file is loaded for execution.

objdump -t XXX.out --> shows which symbol is in which segment
